-- Daisy Group says receives takeover approach
-- By Aashika Jain in Bangalore
-- Wed Aug 13, 2014 02:20AM EDT
-- None



Aug 13 (Reuters) - Daisy Group Plc <DAY.L>, a voice and data services company, said it has received a preliminary takeover approach by a consortium, which includes the company's chief executive.

The AIM-listed company said it received an approach of a possible cash offer of 190 pence per share from Toscafund Asset Management LLP on behalf of the consortium. [ID:nRSM9681Oa]